article.headline: UNC-Greensboro 90, Webber 78
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- Landon Clement scored a game-high 26 points to lead UNC-Greensboro to a 90-78 win against Webber on Monday night. Clement was one of three players to score in double figures for the Spartans (1-1), as Mikko Koivisto scored 18 and Ben Stywall chipped in 12. Stywall also grabbed a game-high 10 rebounds. The Spartans shot 44.9 percent from the field (31 of 69) compared to 41.7 percent (25 of 60) from the Warriors (4-2) en route to victory. The Warriors had five players in double figures, four of which came off the bench. Halston Schaffer and Tyler Hoevanaar scored 12 points each. Both teams turned the ball over 23 times, but the Spartans grabbed 48 rebounds versus 33 from the Warriors.
